    <string name="changelog_title">Changelog</string>
    <string name="changelog_subtitle">See latest changes</string>
    <string name="changelog_content">v1.3.1\n- Trash screen redesigned: thumbnail previews for images, videos, audio, and APKs.\n- Tap in Trash opens files with the preferred app (same as main browser).\n- Long-press in Trash shows a bottom action bar (Restore / Info / Delete).\n- Both app-trash and system-trash sections are always visible, with an empty placeholder when empty.\n- Section headers show an info badge (theme-aware).\n- Empty trash now covers both sections with a combined count confirmation.\n- Info in Trash shows the original path and the auto-delete countdown.\n- Folder item counts now exclude hidden files and label trashed items separately.\n- Fixed image opening via MediaStore URI so gallery apps can swipe between siblings.\n- Default apps dialog now scrolls so buttons are always visible with long lists.\n- Delete confirmation button order changed to: Delete forever / Cancel / Move to trash.\n- Switching to Storage now clears any active selection in Recents.\n\nv1.3.0\n- Recents redesigned with the same row style and long-press selection behavior as Storage.\n- Recents selection actions were streamlined to Locate/Pin/Info (single selection) and Pin/Remove from recents (multi-selection).\n- In Recents, Info is now hidden when selecting 2 or more items.\n- In Recents, selected items can now be removed directly from recents for one or multiple selection.\n- Locate from Recents now jumps to Storage and selects the target file automatically.\n- Visual pin badge is shown directly on pinned recent items.\n- Recents stay ordered by access date, with clear day separators (Today, Yesterday, and date groups).\n- Clear recents now removes only non-pinned items and keeps pinned ones.\n- Auto-discovery no longer repopulates old files after clearing recents.\n- Delete confirmation was reordered (Cancel, Delete permanently, Move to trash) with destructive action highlighted.\n- Open picker More apps now uses the same base filtering approach as add-extension app selection.\n- Storage header was compacted: quick actions moved next to title and a Home button was added.\n- Breadcrumb now uses full width with side margins and wraps to additional lines only when needed.\n- Send from Storage now also supports folder selection and opens compatible apps from the chooser.\n- Share text save now opens a name and type dialog before creating the file.\n- Interactive swipe between Recents and Storage now follows the finger smoothly.\n- Open picker label shortened to More apps for clearer actions.\n\nv1.2.9\n- App name localized by system language.\n- Open picker improved (Show more apps flow).\n- Info action available for single item, including folders.\n- Rename hidden on multi-selection.\n- Quick guide links and GitHub link added to Settings.\n\nv1.2.8\n- Smarter temporary playlist names.\n- Share sheet import with Save here.\n- Moved files are removed from Recents.\n\nv1.2.7\n- Open/default app UX refinements and selection bar adjustments.</string>
